# Security Guidelines

## Mandatory Security Checks

Before ANY commit:
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets (API keys, passwords, tokens)
- [ ] All user inputs validated (class-validator DTOs on backend)
- [ ] NoSQL injection prevention (no raw user input in MongoDB queries)
- [ ] XSS prevention (sanitize output in templates)
- [ ] CSRF protection enabled
- [ ] Authentication/authorization verified on all endpoints
- [ ] Rate limiting on public endpoints
- [ ] Error messages don't leak internal details

## Secret Management

- NEVER hardcode secrets in source code
- ALWAYS use environment variables
- Validate required env vars at startup (NestJS ConfigModule)
- `.env` files are gitignored

```typescript
// WRONG
const secret = 'my-jwt-secret-key';

// CORRECT
const secret = process.env.JWT_SECRET;
if (!secret) throw new Error('JWT_SECRET not configured');
```

## MongoDB-Specific

- Never pass raw user input into query operators (`$where`, `$regex`, etc.)
- Use Mongoose schema validation as second layer
- Sanitize query parameters before building filters
